# 2. わずかな迷い

An: Phew... We discussed a lot of stuff today. I'm exhausted.
An: (But I don't have time to relax right now.)
An: (I have to do this. Starting tonight.)
An: (I have to get them to believe in us. I have to do everything I can to make that happen...!)
An: (All that's left is to figure out how...)
An: *Nod* (I need them to hear that I'm committed to this goal.)
An: (By putting on the best performance I can for them.)
An: (And I'm gonna make a declaration to them the same way Aunt Nagi did.)
An: (I'm gonna tell them that we're going to go beyond her dream...)
An: Alright!
An: (My mind's made up, so I've gotta find a way to get better. I'll start by practicing more on my own and...)
An: Oh, that reminds me...
An: I wonder if Dad's still at the cafe.
Ken: Okay. Then, I'll leave the rest to you.
Ken: Phew... Now that I managed to get ahold of Granny, I should probably get ready to head out.
An: Aha! Thank goodness you're still here.
Ken: Hm? What are you doing here so late? Don't forget that we have practice tomorrow morning.
An: Yeah, I know... But I'm not really in the mood for sleep right now.
An: So, can you watch me practice for a bit? I didn't get to sing much today, so just thirty minutes!
Ken: Alright, fine.
An: Really? Thanks!
An: Then, sit back and listen! Comment when you feel the need!
Ken: Got it.
An: Alright, where's the mic...? Actually, it's pretty late, so I probably shouldn't use it. Anyway, I'll sing...
Ken: (Looks like she's on the right path...)
Ken: (I honestly wasn't sure how An would take the task I gave her.)
Ken: (Especially considering how hard it's been for the locals to talk to her...)
Ken: (I was fairly certain that she'd have trouble seeing them in the same light she used to...)
Ken: (But I may've been wrong about that...)
An: Alright, I'm all set! You ready?!
An: ♪——————!!
Ken: (She sounds good.)
Ken: (I'm not hearing any of the hesitation I did before. She's throwing everything she has into her singing.)
Ken: (If she can keep this up...)
An: ♪——————!!
An: (Yeah, I'm projecting my voice well. But...)
An: (I'll need to do more than just that.)
An: (I need to learn how to have as much energy as Aunt Nagi did that night.)
An: (No, more than that. More than anyone else!)
An: ...
An: (No...! That doesn't matter right now...!)
An: (Focus!)
An: ♪...——————!!
Ken: Hm?
Ken: (What just happened?)
Ken: (Why did she hesitate just now...?)
Ken: (What was she thinking about...?)
An: ♪——————~~!!
Ken: Sorry, An. Stop for a second.
An: ...
An: Why'd you want me to stop, Dad? Was I off-key?
Ken: No, you sounded great. Pitch perfect and flawless rhythm. It's just...
Ken: An.
Ken: Is there something on your mind?
